(42, 19, 22, 40, 22, 12, 12, NULL, 'Judgment and Accountability Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment based on one''s actions. Both passages emphasize the consequences faced by individuals who fail to meet expectations, as seen in the servant''s wickedness and the guest''s lack of a wedding garment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 22, 45, 3, 19, 19, 'Out of thine own mouth will I judge thee', 'Judgment and Guilt Before God', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment based on one''s actions. Both passages emphasize accountability, with the servant judged for his knowledge and the law revealing guilt to all.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 23, 2, 22, 25, 27, 'with usury', 'Usury and Lending Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of usury in lending. Luke 19:23 questions the lack of interest on money lent, while Exodus 22:25-27 forbids charging interest to the poor, highlighting a moral obligation in financial dealings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 23, 5, 23, 19, 20, 'usury', 'Usury and Lending Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of usury in lending. Luke 19:23 refers to the expectation of earning interest, while Deuteronomy 23:19-20 outlines prohibitions against usury among brothers, highlighting differing attitudes towards lending to friends versus strangers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 23, 45, 2, 4, 5, 'that at my coming I might have required', 'Connection of Accountability and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of neglecting responsibility. Luke 19:23 speaks of requiring what is due, while Romans 2:4-5 warns against hardening one''s heart and accumulating wrath.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 24, 42, 12, 20, 20, NULL, 'Accountability and Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in stewardship. In Luke 19:24, the act of taking from one and giving to another emphasizes the expectation of wise management of resources, while Luke 12:20 warns of the futility of hoarding without regard for one''s soul.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 24, 42, 16, 2, 2, NULL, 'Stewardship and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship and accountability in both passages. In Luke 19:24, the act of taking from one steward and giving to another reflects the accountability emphasized in Luke 16:2, where a steward is called to give an account of his management.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 25, 10, 7, 19, 19, NULL, 'Divine Provision and Expectation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s provision and the expectations surrounding it. In both passages, there is an acknowledgment of what is given and the implications for the future, suggesting a continuity in God''s dealings with humanity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 25, 23, 55, 8, 9, 'he hath ten pounds', 'Divine Perspective on Human Understanding', 'This connection highlights the contrast between human expectations and divine wisdom. In Luke, the mention of ''ten pounds'' reflects human valuation, while Isaiah emphasizes that God''s thoughts and ways are far beyond human comprehension.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 25, 42, 16, 2, 2, 'ten pounds', 'Stewardship and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship and the expectation of accountability in both passages. In Luke 19:25, the mention of ''ten pounds'' suggests a responsibility that requires assessment, paralleling the call for accountability in Luke 16:2.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 40, 13, 12, 12, NULL, 'Abundance and Loss Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who have will receive more, while those who lack will lose what they have. This connection highlights a similar theme of reward and loss based on one''s possession.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 40, 21, 43, 43, 'even that he hath shall be taken away', 'Connection of Kingdom and Stewardship', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that what is possessed can be taken away if not utilized properly. Luke 19:26''s notion of taking from those who have not aligns with Matthew 21:43''s warning about the kingdom being taken from one group and given to another that produces fruit.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 42, 8, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Stewardship and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who possess understanding or resources will receive more, while those lacking them will lose even what they appear to have. This connection highlights the importance of how one receives and utilizes what they have.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 63, 1, 8, 8, 'that unto every one which hath shall be given', 'Connection of Reward and Loss', 'This connection highlights the theme of reward based on one''s actions. Both passages emphasize that what one has can be increased or lost depending on their stewardship.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 41, 4, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Wealth and Loss', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who possess will receive more, while those lacking will lose what they have. This connection highlights a similar teaching on the consequences of one''s state of abundance or scarcity.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 9, 2, 30, 30, NULL, 'Honoring and Receiving Blessings', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who honor or possess will receive more, while those who do not will lose what they have. This connection highlights the idea of divine justice and reward based on one''s actions and attitudes.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 26, 9, 15, 28, 28, NULL, 'Loss and Transfer of Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of loss and transfer. In Luke, those who have will receive more, while those who lack will lose what they have. Similarly, in 1 Samuel, the kingdom is taken from Saul and given to someone better.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 42, 19, 14, 14, NULL, 'Rejection of Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of the ruler''s authority. In Luke 19:14, the citizens express their unwillingness for him to reign, which leads to the consequences described in Luke 19:27.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 19, 21, 8, 9, 'enemies', 'Divine Judgment on Enemies', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment against enemies. Both passages emphasize the fate of those who oppose God''s authority, depicting them as subject to severe punishment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 40, 22, 7, 7, 'bring hither, and slay them before me', 'Judgment Against Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the king''s wrath against those who reject his authority. In Luke, the enemies are to be slain, while in Matthew, the king sends armies to destroy the murderers and their city.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 4, 16, 30, 35, 'slay them before me', 'Judgment and Divine Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment against those who reject authority. Both passages depict a severe consequence for those who oppose God''s reign, with Luke emphasizing slaying enemies and Numbers illustrating the earth swallowing dissenters.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 42, 21, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Vengeance and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment against enemies. Both passages emphasize the consequences for those who reject authority, with the first calling for the slaying of enemies and the second referring to days of vengeance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 19, 2, 9, 9, 'bring hither, and slay them before me', 'Judgment of Enemies', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment against enemies. Both passages emphasize the violent consequences for those who oppose the reign of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 27, 34, 1, 8, 8, 'enemies', 'Judgment on Enemies', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of enemies. Luke 19:27 speaks of slaying enemies, while Nahum 1:8 describes making an utter end of them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 42, 9, 51, 51, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem, highlighting a pivotal moment in Jesus'' mission. The phrase ''to go to Jerusalem'' in Luke 9:51 connects directly to the act of ''ascending up to Jerusalem'' in Luke 19:28.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 58, 12, 2, 2, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem and Endurance', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' journey as he ascends to Jerusalem, which foreshadows his ultimate sacrifice. Both passages emphasize the significance of enduring challenges for a greater purpose, culminating in his exaltation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 60, 4, 1, 1, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Connection of Suffering and Ascension', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s journey towards suffering. Both passages emphasize the significance of Christ''s actions in relation to his suffering and the implications for believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 19, 40, 6, 8, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Connection of Will and Journey', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to God''s will. In Luke, Jesus ascends to Jerusalem, indicating his commitment to fulfill his mission, while Psalms expresses a desire to do God''s will, emphasizing the importance of obedience.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 41, 10, 32, 34, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem, highlighting Jesus'' leadership as he goes before his followers. This connection underscores the significance of this journey in the narrative of his impending suffering and death.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 28, 42, 12, 50, 50, 'ascending up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem and Baptism', 'Both passages emphasize a significant journey and a sense of urgency. In Luke 19:28, Jesus is ascending to Jerusalem, while in Luke 12:50, he expresses a feeling of being straitened until his baptism is accomplished, indicating a pivotal moment in his mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
